</span></h1><div class="sc-iAKWXU lesjfG pf-9_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px;--s-lg:0px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-eySxxw fIKYYX pf-10_"><h3 tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-emDsmM BOtMC pf-11_"><i class="sc-hWBuOZ iKxntp pf-12_ pfa pfa-book-open-reader" data-pf-type="Icon"></i>Dr&nbsp;Richard Dune</h3><h3 tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-emDsmM BOtMC pf-13_"><i class="sc-hWBuOZ iKxntp pf-14_ pfa pfa-calendar-days" data-pf-type="Icon"></i>14-08-2023</h3></div></div></div><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Becoming_a_person_of_value_A_fulfilling_journey_beyond_success.jpg?v=1692007520" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Becoming_a_person_of_value_A_fulfilling_journey_beyond_success.jpg?v=1692007520 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Becoming_a_person_of_value_A_fulfilling_journey_beyond_success_1000x.jpg?v=1692007520 768w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Becoming_a_person_of_value_A_fulfilling_journey_beyond_success_500x.jpg?v=1692007520 320w" width="1444" height="757" alt="Becoming a person of value: A fulfilling journey beyond success - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Becoming a person of value: A fulfilling journey beyond success - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-leSONj uTJGF pf-15_"/></div></div></div></div></div><div data-section-id="pf-3199" data-category="Generic Content" data-name="Matcha" data-pf-type="Section" class="sc-jNHqnW kXSKNz pf-16_"><div style="--cw:1170px" class="sc-cqJhZP gRKDwp"><div class="sc-iAKWXU lesjfG pf-17_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:0px;--s-sm:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-eySxxw fIKYYX pf-18_"><p class="sc-dMOJrz cGFGtP pf-19_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-bjztik hIbmEr pf-21_">In the ever-accelerating world of status symbols, financial markers, and social media influencers, Albert Einstein has beautifully articulated an unwavering truth: "Try not to become a person of success, but rather try to become a person of value."<br><br>In this article, <a href="https://www.mandatorytraining.co.uk/pages/dr-richard-dune-blog" target="_blank"><i><span style="color: rgb(0, 71, 178);">Dr Richard Dune</span></i></a> discusses how this idea pushes us to think beyond the conventional paradigms of success, which are so often brief and superficial. He argues that to be of value, however, means to possess an intrinsic worth that stands the test of time, contributing positively to the world and its inhabitants.<br>

</span></p><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-jeraig eTNnJl pf-22_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-bjztik hIbmEr pf-24_">Key definitions
</span></h2><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Key_definitions_17f136cb-1685-4102-af17-817a0fecf956.jpg?v=1692007619" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Key_definitions_17f136cb-1685-4102-af17-817a0fecf956.jpg?v=1692007619 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Key_definitions_17f136cb-1685-4102-af17-817a0fecf956_500x.jpg?v=1692007619 320w" width="1502" height="1002" alt="Becoming a person of value: A fulfilling journey beyond success - Key definitions - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Becoming a person of value: A fulfilling journey beyond success - Key definitions - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-leSONj uTJGF pf-25_"/><p class="sc-dMOJrz cGFGtP pf-26_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-bjztik hIbmEr pf-28_">Before we delve into the subject, let’s define the key terms used in this article:
</span></p><ul style="--text-indent:0;--line-spacing:10px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-eZhRLC dwDNfh pf-29_"><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-dYtuZ fhpFsJ pf-30_"><b>Intrinsic worth</b> - refers to the inherent, essential, or natural value of something or someone. The value exists because of the very nature of the thing or person, not because of external factors or perceptions.
</li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-dYtuZ fhpFsJ pf-32_"><b>Depth</b> - In the context of the article, depth is used to describe a profound understanding or mastery of a particular area or field. Instead of having a superficial or basic knowledge of many things (breadth), depth emphasises a more profound, comprehensive knowledge or skill in specific areas.</li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-dYtuZ fhpFsJ pf-34_"><b>Relationships</b> refer to how two or more people or things are connected or the state of being connected. The article emphasises the quality and depth of human connections and interactions, particularly the bonds formed when prioritising value over success.</li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-dYtuZ fhpFsJ pf-36_"><b>Byproduct</b> - A byproduct is a secondary result, unintended consequence, or incidental outcome of a specific process or action. In the article, success is described as a byproduct of striving for value, meaning success can naturally arise when one's primary focus is on being valuable.</li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-dYtuZ fhpFsJ pf-38_"><b>Introspective</b> - Introspection refers to the examination or observation of one's own mental and emotional processes. A reflective person tends to look inward, reflecting on their thoughts, feelings, and beliefs. The article emphasises the reflective nature of seeking value over success, as it requires individuals to align with their core beliefs and values.</li></ul><p class="sc-dMOJrz cGFGtP pf-40_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-bjztik hIbmEr pf-42_">Each of these terms or concepts contributes to the overarching theme of the article, which champions the importance of striving for personal value over conventional success.
</span></p><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-jeraig eTNnJl pf-43_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-bjztik hIbmEr pf-45_">Depth over breadth

</span></h2><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Depth_over_breadth.jpg?v=1692007704" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Depth_over_breadth.jpg?v=1692007704 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Depth_over_breadth_500x.jpg?v=1692007704 320w" width="960" height="720" alt="Depth over breadth - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Depth over breadth - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-leSONj uTJGF pf-46_"/><p class="sc-dMOJrz cGFGtP pf-47_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-bjztik hIbmEr pf-49_">Becoming a person of value does not necessarily mean having a vast array of skills or being a master of all trades. It implies profound depth in one’s chosen field, skill, or character trait. Depth gives credibility, substance, and longevity. While many people can skim the surface of various pursuits, those who delve deeply are the ones who indeed leave an imprint. Such depth often translates to expertise, trustworthiness, and long-term impact, elements intrinsically tied to personal value.
<br> </span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-jeraig eTNnJl pf-50_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-bjztik hIbmEr pf-52_">Relationships: The heartbeat of value

</span></h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Relationships_The_heartbeat_of_value.jpg?v=1692007788" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Relationships_The_heartbeat_of_value.jpg?v=1692007788 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Relationships_The_heartbeat_of_value_500x.jpg?v=1692007788 320w" width="1272" height="786" alt="Relationships: The heartbeat of value - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Relationships: The heartbeat of value - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-leSONj uTJGF pf-53_"/><p class="sc-dMOJrz cGFGtP pf-54_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-bjztik hIbmEr pf-56_">Relationships take on a different hue when you shift your focus to being valuable. Instead of leveraging connections to climb the corporate or social ladder, the emphasis becomes nurturing, giving, and understanding. The most cherished memories and moments in life are often not linked to achievements but to meaningful interactions with others. By being someone who genuinely adds worth to every interaction, the relationships we cultivate become more profound and enduring.

</span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-jeraig eTNnJl pf-57_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-bjztik hIbmEr pf-59_">Success is a byproduct, not a goal
</span></h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Success_is_a_byproduct_not_a_goal.jpg?v=1692007899" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Success_is_a_byproduct_not_a_goal.jpg?v=1692007899 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Success_is_a_byproduct_not_a_goal_500x.jpg?v=1692007899 320w" width="1336" height="738" alt="Success is a byproduct, not a goal - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Success is a byproduct, not a goal - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-leSONj uTJGF pf-60_"/><p class="sc-bvFjSx yVjXo pf-61_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Focusing on becoming valuable often leads to success as an unintended consequence. Think of some of the most influential figures in history: Marie Curie, Mahatma Gandhi, and Martin Luther King Jr., to name a few. They didn’t set out with success as their primary objective. A cause, a passion, or a curiosity drove them. Their value was evident in their dedication and impact on the world. Success, in terms of recognition and accolades, followed naturally.

<br>
</p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-jeraig eTNnJl pf-63_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-bjztik hIbmEr pf-65_">The anchor in a changing world

</span></h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/The_anchor_in_a_changing_world.jpg?v=1692008002" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/The_anchor_in_a_changing_world.jpg?v=1692008002 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/The_anchor_in_a_changing_world_500x.jpg?v=1692008002 320w" width="1198" height="609" alt="The anchor in a changing world - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="The anchor in a changing world - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-leSONj uTJGF pf-66_"/><p class="sc-bvFjSx yVjXo pf-67_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">The parameters of success change with evolving societal norms, economic fluctuations, and technological advancements. What’s considered successful in one decade may be deemed ordinary in the next. However, value remains a constant anchor, especially when grounded in principles of kindness, integrity, and knowledge. People who embody these values are respected and sought after, irrespective of the changing tides of societal definitions of success.

<br>
</p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-jeraig eTNnJl pf-69_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-bjztik hIbmEr pf-71_">A fulfilling inner journey


</span></h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/A_fulfilling_inner_journey.jpg?v=1692008087" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/A_fulfilling_inner_journey.jpg?v=1692008087 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/A_fulfilling_inner_journey_500x.jpg?v=1692008087 320w" width="1444" height="849" alt="A fulfilling inner journey - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="A fulfilling inner journey - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-leSONj uTJGF pf-72_"/><p class="sc-bvFjSx yVjXo pf-73_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">While success often looks outward for validation (awards, praise, financial gain), value is deeply reflective. It demands an alignment with one's core beliefs and values. This alignment fosters a sense of purpose and fulfilment, leading to genuine happiness and contentment. When prioritising being valuable, you're not constantly looking outside for validation. Instead, you find quiet satisfaction in knowing you’re living a life aligned with your deepest convictions.


<br>
</p><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-jeraig eTNnJl pf-75_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-bjztik hIbmEr pf-77_">Conclusion</span></h2><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Conclusion_f36bf4ce-fb53-4bdc-9aaa-249c0cf26a5f.jpg?v=1692008174" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Conclusion_f36bf4ce-fb53-4bdc-9aaa-249c0cf26a5f.jpg?v=1692008174 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Conclusion_f36bf4ce-fb53-4bdc-9aaa-249c0cf26a5f_500x.jpg?v=1692008174 320w" width="1805" height="1032" alt="Becoming a person of value: A fulfilling journey beyond success - Conclusion - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Becoming a person of value: A fulfilling journey beyond success - Conclusion - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-leSONj uTJGF pf-78_"/><p class="sc-dMOJrz cGFGtP pf-79_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-bjztik hIbmEr pf-81_">While there’s nothing inherently wrong with seeking success, it's crucial to discern the motivation behind this pursuit. If the drive for success is grounded in a deeper desire to add value, then that journey becomes rewarding, irrespective of its material outcomes.<br>

<br>By striving to be individuals of value, we elevate our lives and contribute significantly to the world around us. It’s a call to look beyond the fleeting and superficial and to embrace a more profound, enduring, and ultimately fulfilling measure of one’s life.<br>
